Right in the heart of the city and connecting the sprightly southside with the bustling northside Grattan Bridge is one of the river Liffey‚Äôs true treasures, that offers stunning views of the city. Grattan Bridge is one of the forgotten gems of the city and weather permitting this is where usually find us here at some stage on a Friday night having a slice of üçïafter a few üçª.

This print is part of our ‚ÄúDublin Landmark‚Äù series, a bold and contemporary collection of open edition prints inspired by Ireland‚Äôs heritage, culture and architecture.

Our fine art archival prints are printed on recycled archival paper using archival inks and are guaranteed to retain their vivid colour and striking aesthetic for a lifetime. Designed and printed in our Dublin studio, each print is hand signed to guarantee authenticity. Available in sizes A4 (21x29cm), A3 (29x42cm), A2 (42x59cm) and A1 (59x84cm)

We care deeply about the environment and use only recycled paper and card made from wood free ECF (Elemental Chlorine Free) pulp. All our prints are packaged in clear protective sleeves made from corn starch and are 100% biodegradable.

To keep your print as safe as possible, unframed prints are shipped inside a kraft tube for extra protection. Upon arrival, we would recommend you take your print out of the tube as soon as possible and give it pride of place on your wall.

As part of our Tree Planting Initiative with Mossy Earth, you can now adopt an Irish tree for an additional ‚Ç¨5 as part of your purchase, in a bid to offset your carbon footprint. Simply select the option from the product drop down list. Shortly after, you will be provided with follow up information on your sapling, when and where it‚Äôs been planted and even the GPS coordinates so you can go visit!

Collection option available. Simply select the Pick Up option at checkout.
